race.comment: ECCLESTONE (8) hasn't won for a while but this looks his chance. Tackled a Class 2 off a one-month let-up last start over this trip at Eagle Farm and did a good job to be beaten just 1.2 lengths after leading. Will take a lot from that hit-out and in this company will be very tough to catch. MIDNIGHT DRIFTER (1) came from the clouds to score over 1400m at Grafton last start. Very effective at this trip and must be considered despite the 61kgs. FIRST MAN (6) can improve on a modest first-up effort at Gatton nine days ago. CAPE CRUSADER (2) resumes straight up to 1400m. Two wins last prep and has placed first up in the past.
